senses.sense: Expression of surprise.
examples: Oh! I didn't see you there.

senses.sense: Expression of wonder, amazement, or awe.
Expression of understanding, affirmation, recognition, or realization.
examples: Oh, so that's how it works.

senses.sense: A word to precede an offhand or annoyed remark.
A word to precede an added comment or afterthought.
examples: Oh, and don't forget your coat.

senses.sense: An invocation or address (similar to the vocative in languages with noun declension), often with a term of endearment.
Exclamation for drama or emphasis (often poetic).
Expression of pain. See ouch.
Space filler or extra syllable, especially in (popular) music.
(interrogative) Expression of mild scepticism.
A word to mark a spoken phrase as imaginary.
examples: What if he says "Oh, I need to see your ID"?

senses.sense: An utterance of oh; a spoken expression of surprise, acknowledgement, etc.
(intransitive) To utter the interjection oh; to express surprise, etc.
the letter O, o (more commonly spelled o)
the digit 0 (especially in representations of speech)
simple past tense and past participle of oh
A small red or yellow berry growing on the shrub Vaccinium reticulatum of volcanic parts of the Hawaiian islands of Hawaii and Maui, or the shrub itself.
Either of two flowering trees of the myrtle family, especially
in Hawaii: the lehua, Metrosideros polymorpha (native to Hawaii)
the Malay apple, Syzygium malaccense, (native to Southeast Asia, introduced throughout the tropics).
